JOHANNESBURG - While business is reportedly booming for vendors outside the Nasrec conference centre in Johannesburg, vendors in Vilikazi Street, just a few kilometres away, are complaining. They say those in the conference precinct are taking away their business. IN PICTURES: Day two of the ANC elective conference Vilakazi Street is known for having housed struggle heroes like Nelson Mandela and Desmond Tutu. It is also home to the iconic Hector Peterson memorial site. The street also boasts some of the best restaurants in Soweto. eNCA